# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .env.example — Template for your API credentials
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# HOW TO USE THIS FILE:
#   1. Make a copy of this file named ".env" (just .env, no "example")
#   2. Replace the placeholder values with your real credentials
#   3. NEVER share your .env file or commit it to GitHub!
#      (It's already listed in .gitignore — keep it that way)
#
# WHAT IS A .env FILE?
#   It's a simple text file that stores secret values (like passwords and API keys).
#   Each line is: KEY=value
#   The "dotenv" library reads this file and loads these values into Python.
#   This way, your secrets never end up hardcoded in your Python script.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── ANTHROPIC (CLAUDE AI) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Get your API key at: https://console.anthropic.com
#   1. Sign up or log in
#   2. Click "API Keys" in the left sidebar
#   3. Click "Create Key"
#   4. Copy the key and paste it below
#   5. ⚠️  You'll only see the key once — save it somewhere safe!
#
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=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


# ── INOREADER ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Inoreader requires 3 things: an App ID, an App Key, and an access token.
#
# HOW TO GET YOUR APP ID AND APP KEY:
#   1. Go to https://www.inoreader.com/developers
#   2. Log in to your Inoreader account
#   3. Click "Create New Application"
#   4. Fill in the name (e.g., "Daily Curator") and description
#   5. For "OAuth2 Redirect URI" enter: https://localhost
#   6. After creating, you'll see your App ID and App Key on the app page
#
INOREADER_APP_ID=1000007033
INOREADER_APP_KEY=937DU9jAhsfidYZN5QtF1hPt3J40b8JW


# HOW TO GET YOUR ACCESS TOKEN:
#
#   Inoreader uses OAuth2 for authentication. The easiest way for personal use
#   is to generate a token using their OAuth2 flow. Here are two options:
#
#   OPTION A — Use the Inoreader API Explorer (Easiest):
#   1. Go to: https://www.inoreader.com/developers/api-explorer
#   2. Authenticate with your account
#   3. The explorer shows your active token — copy it
#
#   OPTION B — Manual OAuth2 flow:
#   1. Open this URL in your browser (replace YOUR_APP_ID):
#      https://www.inoreader.com/oauth2/auth?client_id=YOUR_APP_ID&redirect_uri=https://localhost&response_type=code&scope=read
#   2. Log in and authorize the app
#   3. You'll be redirected to https://localhost?code=SOME_CODE
#      Copy the "code" value from the URL
#   4. Exchange it for a token by running this in your terminal (replace values):
#      curl -X POST https://www.inoreader.com/oauth2/token \
#        -d "code=PASTE_CODE_HERE&redirect_uri=https://localhost&grant_type=authorization_code" \
#        -u "YOUR_APP_ID:YOUR_APP_KEY"
#   5. Copy the "access_token" from the response
#
#   NOTE: Tokens expire after some time. If the script suddenly stops working,
#   you may need to refresh your token using the refresh_token value.
#
INOREADER_TOKEN=1a9c9944d88d9147c032a464eb9c4ec1e8e7a2e8
INOREADER_REFRESH_TOKEN=ac52584519f5bfc25a0ea57b5f380def82f705e2
APIFY_API_TOKEN=apify_api_RXhEuRm1md6cZbWHC86rYVJ9ZV6yKX1jiXPV
